        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 2:47PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 247 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm very
near Spearville, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Spearville and Bellefont around 250 PM CDT.
Offerle around 255 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of this storm include Kinsley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
